European Coal Derivatives Retreat 0.8%, Falling for Third Day

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-04-13T08:28:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/european-coal-derivatives-retreat-0-8-falling-for-third-day.html
Benchmark European coal derivatives
fell for a third day.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year declined $1.10, or 0.8 percent, to $129 a
metric ton by 9:20 a.m. in  London . The contract, used to bet on
or hedge against future prices, has fallen 3.4 percent this
week.  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
 GFI Group Inc. (GFIG) , Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
